= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =
bounce_recipients listname <<TAG
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
listname, required, is an email list at this site (not GLOBAL)
<<TAG, if specified, provides more than one line of data (here file)
= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =

EXAMPLE:
configset listname bounce_recipients << ENDTAG
joe@blow.org
ENDTAG


Who will receive error messages for this list?  Majordomo will internally
forward mail received at the -owner address to all of these addresses if
the mail is identified as a bounce message.  If this variable is unset,
bounces will be forwarded to the list owners.

See Also:
   help configset owners (for how to specify the list owner)

For a list of all help topics send this one-line message
   help topics
to the server at $MJ
